### CityVoice – Admin API Tests (User Role Management + Category Management)
### Compatible with: IntelliJ HTTP Client, VS Code REST Client
### Base URL: http://localhost:8080/api

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api
@adminEmail = admin@cityvoice.vn
@adminPassword = Admin@123

# ─── 0. AUTHENTICATE AS ADMIN ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Run this first to get the admin access token.

### 0a. Admin login (saves access token globally)
# @name adminLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/staff/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{adminEmail}}",
  "password": "{{adminPassword}}"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("adminToken", response.body.data.accessToken);
  client.test("Login OK", () => client.assert(response.status === 200));
%}


# ─── 1. USER ROLE MANAGEMENT ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1a. List all available roles
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/roles
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 1b. List all users (Admin only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 1b. Promote a citizen to staff
# Replace <userId> with the actual UUID of the citizen from the DB.
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admin/users/a26871a5-37fe-4f17-a055-eb5f0a43ddb6/role
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "staff"
}

###

### 1c. Demote a staff back to citizen
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admin/users/a26871a5-37fe-4f17-a055-eb5f0a43ddb6/role
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "citizen"
}

###

### 1d. Assign manager role
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admin/users/a26871a5-37fe-4f17-a055-eb5f0a43ddb6/role
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "manager"
}

###

### 1e. Update role without token – expect 403
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admin/users/<userId>/role
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "staff"
}

###

### 1f. Update role with invalid userId – expect 404
PUT {{baseUrl}}/admin/users/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/role
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "staff"
}


# ─── 2. CATEGORY MANAGEMENT ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 2a. Create a new category (Admin only)
# @name createCategory
POST {{baseUrl}}/categories
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Whoops",
  "slug": "whoops",
  "iconKey": "icon-whoops",
  "active": true
}

> {%
  client.global.set("categoryId", response.body.data.id);
  client.test("Category created", () => client.assert(response.status === 201));
%}

###

### 2b. Duplicate slug – expect 409
POST {{baseUrl}}/categories
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Pothole Duplicate",
  "slug": "pothole",
  "active": true
}

###

### 2c. Update an existing category (rename + keep active)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/categories/9
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Road Pothole",
  "slug": "test",
  "iconKey": "icon-road-pothole",
  "active": true
}

###

### 2d. Disable a category (soft-delete via active = false)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/categories/1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Road Pothole",
  "slug": "pothole",
  "iconKey": "icon-road-pothole",
  "active": false
}

###

### 2e. List ALL categories including disabled ones (Admin only)
# Expect: ALL categories returned including inactive ones.
GET {{baseUrl}}/categories/all
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 2f. Verify disabled category is excluded from public list
# Expect: the disabled category is NOT in the result.
GET {{baseUrl}}/categories

###

### 2g. List all categories without token – expect 403
GET {{baseUrl}}/categories/all

###

### 2h. Create category without token – expect 403
POST {{baseUrl}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Unauthorized Category",
  "slug": "unauthorized",
  "active": true
}

###

### 2i. Update non-existent category – expect 404
PUT {{baseUrl}}/categories/9999
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ghost",
  "slug": "ghost",
  "active": true
}
